    {
        "content": "<p>Should I use <code>IsOpen</code> or <code>Open</code>?</p>",
        "id": 323389167,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1674611231
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are we eschewing <code>Is</code> for some reason?</p>",
        "id": 323399188,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1674619530
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It seems that <code>compact</code> was renamed to <code>is_compact</code> some time ago, so probably I should use <code>IsOpen</code>.</p>",
        "id": 323399972,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1674620412
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Is</code> is used all over the place, see for instance <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsSymmOp#doc\">docs4#IsSymmOp</a> and friends.</p>",
        "id": 323402979,
        "sender_full_name": "Frédéric Dupuis",
        "timestamp": 1674623133
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I remember that there was some discussion about <code>is</code> but I don't remember if it was about adding <code>is</code> or removing <code>is</code>.</p>",
        "id": 323403488,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1674623581
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What should I do with the names for <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/Lim\">docs#Lim</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/Lim'\">docs#Lim'</a>, and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/lim\">docs#lim</a>?</p>",
        "id": 323406601,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1674625960
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I believe the consensus is rename <code>has_foo</code> to <code>Foo</code> but leave <code>is_foo</code> as <code>IsFoo</code> unless there's a compelling reason for alignment to Lean 4 core/std conventions?</p>\n<p>This section of the naming wiki is thus far incomplete however.</p>",
        "id": 323406700,
        "sender_full_name": "Arien Malec",
        "timestamp": 1674626033
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's the best consensus on this which amounts to the above:</p>\n<p><a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/ENnReal/near/312549431\">https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/ENnReal/near/312549431</a></p>",
